						               													<description>Be the owner of a mining company and go after the gold before your friends. Hire more miners, bribe miners and steal ore from friends. Almost anything goes in the Gold Rush.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How Game Works?&amp;#10;Each player gets a starting miner that cannot be fired or bribed by another player.&amp;#10;This miner has the actions to mine and reserve a trading card.&amp;#10;Being possible to do both only if the letter says.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When mining, if the mined ore has the time symbol, you can only reveal it on your next turn, if you don't, you can reveal it and use it on the same turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When reserving a charter, it is possible to pay to use it. When paying, you can use it and take effect immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is possible to hire new miners, some are better and some are worse. But it's always good to have a lot of workers, because they are the ones who do the actions in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is possible to equip workers with pickaxes to increase the amount of mining, being able to pull more cards when mining.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with 3 gold wins the game. Gold nuggets are worth 1/3 of gold, so we need 3 gold nuggets to get one gold.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If all possible actions of the players end and no one has the 3 gold, whoever has the most gold wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
